ns. Theoretical doctrine and practical experience are integrated in chapters on establishing political authority, organizing civil administration, reestablishing law and order, asserting humanitarianism, providing military security, and local acceptance of external authority. The result is both a review of past missions and a dialogue about the current and future politics of peace-maintenance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Peace.2bisacsh1 aAdibe, Clement E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBratt, Duane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChopra, Jarat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChopra, Jarat, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCousens, Richard P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrocker, Chester A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonini, Antonio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnight, W. Andy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorphet, Sally, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlunkett, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z97831107842680 cprintz978155587756940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978168585172940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781685851729423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781685851729/original  a978-3-11-078426-8  Lynne Rienner Press Complete Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_S